<br>
IMPORTANT:  For you internet newbs, make sure to use a program to cut down on the screenshot size.  EQ makes 1MB bitmap (BMP) files.  The first thing to do is convert them to JPG (will decrease to around 300KB, or a 3rd the size).  Then change the dimensions to around 640 x 480 or even 800 x 600 (most people play EQ at 800 x 600 or 1024 x 768, but really there's no reason for your uploaded SS to be that big).  Also, sometimes just a small portion of your SS is what you want people to see, cut and paste that portion into a new file -- people will love you for it.<br>
<br>
<br>
2) Once you have a file uploaded, ANYONE on the net can see it if you link to it.  You just have to know the full path of the server and the subdirectory of your files.<br>
<br>
Example of my ISP (fake):  http://www.mywebserver.net/public/smileyguy01/myeqpics<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
3) Ezboard is nice because you don't have to know HTML to link to pictures, you can just use their built in EzCodes.  Images can be linked using &quot;[ image ] path-to-image [ / image ]&quot; (take out the spaces).<br>
<br>
example: [ image ] http://www.mywebserver.net/public/smileyguy01/myeqpics/train.jpg [ / image ]<br>
<br>
will produce: <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mulzet.com/eq/train.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
4) Once you have this down pat you can make yourself a little signature file like you see so many people have and then link to it in your EZBoard profile.<br>
